(5, 1, '2007-09-09 15:09:58', '2007-09-09 20:09:58', '<img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1376/1351317709_14c823d7f6.jpg" height="500" width="375" />\r\n\r\nDogora welcomes you to my new blog!\r\n\r\nStay tuned for exiting news, toy reviews, and other fun stuff!', 'Welcome to my Blog!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome-to-my-blog', '', '', '2007-09-09 15:10:35', '2007-09-09 20:10:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=5', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(9, 1, '2007-09-24 22:03:21', '2007-09-25 03:03:21', '<img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1440/1435363707_824cded323.jpg" height="500" width="355" />\r\n\r\nMonster Mash at Super 7!\r\n\r\nSuper7 is proud to present the Halloween Monster Mash custom art show, featuring the custom figures of a variety of artists from both sides of the Pacific! Western and Eastern artists come together to create the coolest collection of customs ready to haunt your shelf for the month of October.\r\n\r\nThis show will be the first, last and only release ever for the Nathan Jurevicius'' Fauna characters. Direct from MTV Canada and Nathan himself, these three monster miscreants will only be released here, and this will be a rare chance to handle these near extinct species.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of little known species, a new Beetle has been found in the remote wilderness of Japan - Beetlar! This orange vinyl figure with black and silver has never been released before and will make it''s worldwide debut at the Monster Mash show.\r\n\r\nAnother dramatic debut is the latest top secret figure from the twisted bubble-gum mind of Le Merde. A fan favorite, you know Le Merde has the rock on lock, Burger Buns on the brain and plenty hidden up his sleeves. Don''t miss your chance to own the latest addition to the Le Merde arsenal of awesome.\r\n\r\nNot to be outdone, we present a collection of custom figures from the Super7 friends and family kaiju support network. Heavy hitters Paul Kaiju, Kathie Olivas, Koji Harmon, Kyoka Ikeda, Brian Flynn, Hiro Hayashi, Joe Huerta, Josh Herbolsheimer and Leecifer rub elbows and swap paint with Skullbrain.org regulars and SF locals for a fun filled evening of colorful vinyl chaos.', 'Monster Mash!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'monster-mash', '', '', '2007-09-24 22:03:21', '2007-09-25 03:03:21', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=9', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(10, 1, '2007-10-08 00:30:48', '2007-10-08 05:30:48', '<img width="375" src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1211/1445641456_a12bcc451d.jpg" height="500" />\r\n\r\nJust wanted to say thank to everyone who attended Monster Mash,\r\n\r\nand to all those who snagged some of seriously amazing stuff , and some of mine.\r\n\r\nIt was an honor to be included in a show with so many amazing artists.\r\n\r\nIÂ wish I could have been there!\r\n\r\nBig thanks to Super7 as well, and every thing they do to make collecting and customizing kaiju so fun!\r\n\r\nPics of the gig are up on <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/super7/">Super 7''s Flickr</a>.\r\n\r\nYeah!', 'Thanks for Attending Monster Mash!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thanks-for-attending-monster-mash', '', '', '2007-10-08 09:58:37', '2007-10-08 14:58:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=10', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(11, 1, '2007-10-19 18:33:12', '2007-10-19 23:33:12', 'I just received this set of ILANENA EMUPAIYA monsters released at Pachikaijusummit 2007.I''ve seen the larger versions, but I''m a total fan of mini size. They are pink, yet actually glow in the dark.\r\n\r\n<img width="439" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2146/1642800748_df53045fdb.jpg" height="361" style="width: 439px; height: 361px" />\r\n\r\nL to R we have Space eel Metorokabyan, H Hydrogen beast,and my fave of the bunch Fifth Dimension Monster BETARUS who is all over the place! Just another nice day hanging out on the putting green without their clubs.\r\n\r\n<img align="left" width="180" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2318/1642797232_41f08a90c7_m.jpg" height="240" /> <img width="180" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2194/1642799526_464efb2415_m.jpg" height="240" /> <img width="180" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2195/1641922457_4107c12989_m.jpg" height="240" />\r\n\r\nIt''s my understanding that these are based on old made-up monsters (Patchi-Kaiju) immortalized on playing cards back in the 70''s.\r\n\r\nILANENA has also made a few other color ways I think I will need to get.These are a total pocket size treat.\r\n\r\nCheck out BETARUS from the rear. Ain''t he one cute messed up fifth dimensional baby!\r\n\r\n<img width="180" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2038/1642798806_fccfc4ccd9_m.jpg" height="240" />', 'Good things come in small packages of three!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'good-things-come-in-small-packages-of-three', '', '', '2008-04-08 11:47:05', '2008-04-08 16:47:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=11', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(12, 1, '2007-12-23 20:18:15', '2007-12-24 01:18:15', 'To all! Hope everyone gets the squishy monster toys they desire,\r\n\r\ngood cheer,Â  and more!\r\n\r\nI was in the spirit...\r\n\r\nHere''s a frosted candy Kaiju surprise...\r\n\r\n<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2255/2131026189_703d5bf367.jpg" height="500" width="333" />', 'Merry Christmas!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'merry-christmas', '', '', '2007-12-23 20:18:15', '2007-12-24 01:18:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=12', 0, 'post', '', 0),
