(681, 1, '2010-08-26 22:04:45', '2010-08-27 05:04:45', 'I had been a collector of squeeky toy style elephants for a few years.\r\n\r\nIt seems there are so many varieties, sizes, and styles. I am constantly seeing ones I never knew existed.\r\n\r\nThis was my main inspiration in making Boss Carrion. He would fit the Elephants and the Kaiju.\r\n\r\nHe was cute, gross, and weird.\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-662" href="http://localhost/pk-new/?attachment_id=662"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-662" title="The Family" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/The-Family-600x449.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="269" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe arms, legs, head, and fish all came apart and were held on with wooden pegs so I could test\r\n\r\nthe sitting position and movement range.\r\n\r\nI didn''t have any sketches, the sculpt rolled out of my mind very smoothly.\r\n\r\nHere''s a shot of the original sculpt, still very raw.\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-663" href="http://localhost/pk-new/?attachment_id=663"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-663" title="BC2R" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/BC2R-375x500.jpg" alt="" width="375" height="500" /></a>\r\n\r\nI had decided while sculpting that some form of creature was needed on his rear.\r\n\r\nHe was made of various fused animal parts. I was inspired by a certain Kaiju named "Magnetudon" from a 70''s TV show called\r\n\r\n"Spectraman"and decided on a fish. Magnetudon had a catfish for a tail!\r\n\r\nI had gone through about 3 different tail fish before I settled on the last one.\r\n\r\nOne dropped and broke, one got burned, and this one failed my approval.\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-664" href="http://localhost/pk-new/?attachment_id=664"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-664" title="Fish" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Fish-374x500.jpg" alt="" width="374" height="500" /></a>\r\n\r\nTesting sitting pose.\r\n\r\n<a rel="attachment wp-a