(899, 1, '2011-01-25 10:23:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<strong>Q: What exactly is Boss Carrion?</strong>\r\n\r\nA: Boss Carrion is a demon composed of various animal corpses and full of worms.\r\n\r\n<strong>Q:How often are Boss Carrion Releases? Why are they always sold out?</strong>\r\n\r\nA: I keep releases very random. I can never really say. Many people think I should constantly have a back-stock, but it doesn''t work that way. I do it like the Japanese toy producers. each release is a song. Never performed twice. Each run is a very limited piece of art. There are specific Japanese vinyl toys it took me 2-3 years to find for my collection. It makes collecting fresh and fun if you really like it. Many people sell off their collections after a year, so why flood the aftermarket?\r\n\r\n<strong>Q: Why can''t I order a one-of-a-kind custom Boss from you? Or a blank?\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nA:If I do one for you, I have to do one for everybody. I might possibly do a blank release in the future, or possibly a custom show. i am also planning to do lotteries for one off Bosses. it''s more fair.\r\n\r\n<strong>Q: Are you planning more vinyls?</strong>\r\n\r\nA: Yes I am currently sculpting some.\r\n\r\n<strong>Q: Will you paint my western platform toy for an exhibit?</strong>\r\n\r\nA: I put MUCH work into customizing toys. Intense work people aren''t willing to spend on and the percentage of what most galleries take.\r\n\r\nPlus, it depends on how much I like the piece really.\r\n\r\n<strong>Q: Will you custom paint my Japan made Vinyl?</strong>\r\n\r\nA: It depends on what you want. If you let me go nuts it works better. many people have special requests beyond my regular styles and it often turns into a nightmare for both parties.\r\n\r\nif you know what you want, it''s usually a win.', 'Paulkaiju FAQ', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2011-01-25 10:23:21', '2011-01-25 18:23:21', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=899', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(900, 1, '2011-01-25 10:11:41', '2011-01-25 18:11:41', '<strong>Q:How often are Boss Releases? Why are they always sold out?</strong>\n\nA: Very random. I can never really say. Many people think I should constantly have a back-stock, but it doesn''t work that way. I do it like the Japanese toy producers. each release is a song. Never performed twice. Each run is a very limited piece of art. There are specific Japanese vinyl toys it took me 2-3 years to find. It makes collecting fresh and fun if you really like it.\n\n<strong>Q: Why can''t I order a one-of-a-kind custom Boss from you? Or a blank?\n</strong>\n\nA: I have to do one for you, I have to do one for everybody. I might possibly do a blank release in the future, or possibly a custom show.\n\n<strong>Q: Are you planning more vinyls?</strong>\n\nA: Yes I am currently sculpting some.\n\n<strong>Q: Will you paint my western platform toy for an exhibit?</strong>\n\nA: No. Not anymore. I put a LOT of work into customizing toys. The kind of intense work people aren''t willing to spend on.', 'Paulkaiju FAQ', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '899-revision', '', '', '2011-01-25 10:11:41', '2011-01-25 18:11:41', '', 899, 'http://localhost/pk-new/blog/899-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
