(1704, 1, '2012-03-12 11:40:39', '2012-03-12 18:40:39', 'Thanks to all who helped, and attended my show "Paulyvinyl state of mind" March 3rd.\r\n\r\nGino, the entire TAG staff, Melissa, Howie Pyro, and all my friends made it so special!\r\n\r\nIt was one heck of a month''s scramble to get together I''ll tell you that!\r\n\r\nI wish I would have had more but alas time made it all an uphill climb.\r\n\r\nI''m glad to hear Voodoo went to a nice home. I miss him already!\r\n\r\nBig thanks to Matt Walker of <a href="http://www.monsterkolorstore.com/">Monster Kolor</a> and <a href="http://nebulon5.bigcartel.com/">Nebulon5 </a>\r\n\r\nfor making this big one a smooth operation without a scratch!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/pk-new/blog/paulyvinyl-thanks-pollen-kaiser/attachment/cleared/" rel="attachment wp-att-1706"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1706" title="cleared" alt="" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/cleared-374x500.jpg" width="374" height="500" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt was a blast beyond words.\r\n\r\nSome articles!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://shop.toyartgallery.com/-c-33">LA Weekly</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.vinylpulse.com/2012/03/seen-paul-kaiju-pauly-vinyl-state-of-mind-toy-art-gallery.html#more">Vinyl Pulse</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.spankystokes.com/2012/03/recap-paulyvinyl-state-of-mind-solo.html">Spankystokes</a>\r\n\r\nThere''s a painting, some wall sculptures and Pollen Kaiser Tshirts left at TAG. Go <a href="http://shop.toyartgallery.com/-c-33">GET</a>!\r\n\r\nThe shirt design was done in collaboration with Super-Junk, based on a sketch by me, and produced by TAG.\r\n\r\nIt is in celebration of the upcoming "Pollen Kaiser" vinylÂ  figure sculpted by me, and also being produced by TAG.\r\n\r\nMore info on this big figure soon!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://shop.toyartgallery.com/product_toy_info/-c-33/paul-kaiju-pollen-kaiser-t-shirt-black-p-1507"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-1712" title="Print" alt="" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/pollen-kaiser1-416x500.jpg" width="250" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '"Paulyvinyl" Thanks! Pollen Kaiser!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paulyvinyl-thanks-pollen-kaiser', '', '', '2013-08-13 15:45:45', '2013-08-13 22:45:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost/pk-new/?p=1704', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1699, 1, '2012-02-28 15:27:01', '2012-02-28 22:27:01', 'Please join me March 3rd at Toy Art Gallery for my first LA solo show!\r\n\r\nI''ve been working hard on this one. Prepare for many surprises!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.toyartgallery.com/shows/current-shows/03022012-paul-kaiju/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1700" title="PAULYVINYL-livingproof" src="http://localhost/pk-new/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/PAULYVINYL-livingproof-375x500.jpg" alt="" width="375" height="500" /></a>\r\n\r\nToy Art Gallery is proud to present â€œPaulyvinyl State of Mindâ€ by the legendary Paul Kaiju! Paulâ€™s work needs no introduction; as a top-notch painter, sculptor, and toy designer he has taken the toy world by storm with his extremely original designs that are influenced by everything from Japanese Kaiju to 60â€™s Sci-Fi to cheap squeaky toys. Be it Japanese soft vinyl or hand-casted resin, Paulâ€™s creations are truly unique and exquisitely crafted. He now brings this expertise to his first solo show at Toy Art Gallery with a multitude of his various characters in one-offs and editions in vinyl and resin, along with some big surprises!\r\n\r\nâ€œPAULYVINYLâ€ is a limited engagement and opens Saturday, Mar. 3rd and runs through Mar. 18th. There will be an opening reception from 7-11 PM on Mar. 3rd with drinks, music, and good company. Join us at Toy Art Galleryâ€™s new showroom located at 7571 Melrose Ave. Hollywood CA 90046.\r\n\r\nPURCHASING INFO: Tickets to purchase work from PAULYVINYL will be distributed FIRST COME, FIRST SERVE starting at 12 NOON on Sat, Mar. 3rd. One ticket per person. Please claim your place in line by 6:30PM prior to 7PM opening. Any remaining work will go online at <a href="http://shop.toyartgallery.com/">shop.toyartgallery.com</a> the following day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '"Paulyvinyl State of Mind" at Toy Art Gallery', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'paulyvinyl-state-of-mind-at-toy-art-gallery', '', '', '2012-02-28 15:27:01